<treatmentCitationGroup id="AB0C0C38FFCDFF9C6BB0FC38FE44FB82" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">
<treatmentCitation id="0ABD0D07FFCDFF9C6BB0FC38FD00FBA3" box="[151,734,1013,1035]" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCDFF9C6BB0FC38FD00FBA3" authority="Andre, 1881: 57" authorityName="Andre" authorityPageNumber="57" authorityYear="1881" box="[151,734,1013,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Myrmecocystus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="albicans" variety="viaticoides">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCDFF9C6BB0FC38FE4DFBA3" box="[151,403,1013,1035]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">Myrmecocystus albicans</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCDFF9C6AECFC3BFDE7FBA3" box="[459,569,1013,1035]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">viaticoides</emphasis>
André, 1881:57
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
.Combination in 
<treatmentCitation id="0ABD0D07FFCDFF9C68B2FC3BFB0DFBA3" author="Emery, C." box="[917,1235,1013,1035]" page="263" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" year="1925">
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCDFF9C68B2FC3BFB0DFBA3" authority=": Emery, 1925: 263" authorityName=": Emery" authorityPageNumber="263" authorityYear="1925" box="[917,1235,1013,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Cataglyphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCDFF9C68B2FC3BFBD1FBA3" box="[917,1039,1013,1035]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">Cataglyphis</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCDFF9C6F07FC38FB0DFBA3" author="Emery, C." box="[1056,1235,1013,1035]" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" pagination="1 - 302" refId="ref7075" refString="Emery, C. (1925) Hymenoptera, Fam. Formicidae, subfam. Formicinae. In: Wytsman, P. (Ed.), Genera Insectorum. Fasc. 183, pp. 1 - 302." type="book chapter" year="1925">Emery, 1925:263</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
. Raised to species: 
<treatmentCitation id="0ABD0D07FFCDFF9C6BE0FBDAFE48FB82" author="Arnol'di, K. V." box="[199,406,1044,1066]" page="1809" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" year="1964">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCDFF9C6BE0FBDAFE48FB82" author="Arnol'di, K. V." box="[199,406,1044,1066]" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" pagination="1800 - 1815" refId="ref6133" refString="Arnol'di, K. V. (1964) Higher and specialized representatives of the ant genus Cataglyphis (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) in the fauna of the USSR. [In Russian.]. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 43, 1800 - 1815." type="journal article" year="1964">Arnol'di, 1964:1809</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C306789DFFCDFF9C6BB0FB98FBCCFB72" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFCDFF9C6BB0FB98FBCCFB72" blockId="7.[151,1436,1110,1243]" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">
The collection of this species at Rawdhat Khorim represents the first record known for 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCDFF9C6F79FB98FB2EFBC7" box="[1118,1264,1110,1135]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
and the second record for the Arabian Peninsula. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCDFF9C690AFBB4FC80FB3B" author="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D. &amp; Sharaf, M. R. &amp; Van Harten T." box="[557,862,1146,1171]" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" pagination="405 - 474" refId="ref6877" refString="Collingwood, C. A., Agosti, D., Sharaf, M. R. &amp; Van Harten T. (2011) Order Hymenoptera, Family Formicidae. Arthropod Fauna of the UAE, 4, 405 - 474." type="journal article" year="2011">
Collingwood 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCDFF9C69ECFBB5FCD7FB3B" box="[715,777,1146,1171]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">et al.</emphasis>
(2011)
</bibRefCitation>
reported it from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCDFF9C6F14FBB4FBAEFB3B" box="[1075,1136,1146,1171]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">UAE</collectingCountry>
. At Rawdhat Khorim, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCDFF9C6EA5FBB5FECEFB1F" baseAuthorityName="Andre" baseAuthorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Cataglyphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viaticoides">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCDFF9C6EA5FBB5FECEFB1F" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">C. viaticoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common species found throughout the year and abundant from June to October, with a peak in September. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCDFF9C6A3CFB0CFDFCFB73" baseAuthorityName="Andre" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[283,546,1218,1243]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Cataglyphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viaticoides">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCDFF9C6A3CFB0CFDFCFB73" box="[283,546,1218,1243]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">Cataglyphis viaticoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was often observed foraging on 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCDFF9C68B5FB0DFBCCFB72" box="[914,1042,1219,1242]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="572">
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCDFF9C68B5FB0DFBD3FB72" box="[914,1037,1219,1242]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Calotropis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="572" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">C. procera</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
